A base nacional comum curricular e o professor: um olhar a partir da relação ensinoemocao e do ensinoemigualdade
The National Common Curriculum and the teacher: an analysis from the perspective of teaching-learning and teaching-empathy
This article presents a study that analyzes the National Common Core Curriculum (BNCC) from the perspective of teaching-learning and teaching-empathy. The present document presents a study conducted in the context of a research project that aimed to produce knowledge on the implementation of the National Common Core Curriculum in public schools in the State of Espírito Santo (Brazil). The main objective of the study was to understand the perception of the teachers about the National Common Core Curriculum, as well as its implementation. It was conducted a bibliographic and documental analysis of the BNCC and a survey with 60 teachers from the public network of the state of Espírito Santo. The data were analyzed from the perspective of teaching-learning and teaching-empathy. It was concluded that the National Common Core Curriculum is an important instrument to ensure the equity of learning for all students, however, the implementation of the document is still in its incipient stage in the Brazilian schools, and it is necessary to broaden the debate on the theme to provide conditions for the implementation of the National Common Core Curriculum in the Brazilian schools.

Jorge Ferreira, Federal University of Bahia, Salvador, Brazil
